## When to use this pattern
This pattern should be used when you need to ask the user for numeric values such as:
{{ 
    onsList({
        "items": [
            {
                "text": 'the quantity of objects or people (e.g. bedrooms, visitors, employees etc.)'
            },
            {
                "text": 'financial figures (e.g. salaries, expenditure, turnover etc.)'
            },
            {        
                "text": 'estimated percentages (e.g. the percentage of female employees etc.)'
            },
            {        
                "text": 'volumes and measurements (e.g. the size of a workspace etc.)'
            }
        ]
    }) 
}}

## How to use this pattern
Use the [input component](/components/input) and set the type to `number` to add the correct pattern to trigger a numeric keypad on touch devices.

Use the [input width override utility class](/components/input#width-constrained) to set the width of the input when the maximum size of the answer is known.  The class won't limit the number of digits the user can enter, but will help the user understand what they should enter.

